# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

`llama.cpp` has an extensible system for handling model-specific chat template formats in `common/chat.cpp`. Each specialized handler is a static function that manually formats messages according to a model's expected prompt structure, registered in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` which uses marker-based detection on the raw Jinja template source string.

The Mistral Instruct v0.3 format (`[INST]`/`[/INST]` delimiters without `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`) is not currently handled as a specialized template. Adding a dedicated handler ensures correct prompt formatting for Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 and compatible models.

No changes to `common/chat.h` are needed — `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` (the first enum value) is the correct format for this simple text-only handler.

---

## Critical File

- **`common/chat.cpp`** — Two locations require new code (see below)

